snippet.textDisplay: The fact that we're lucky enough to have someone out there like Jenna who is willing to reupload a video to give context is something that I feel like a lot of fans don't appreciate. When most YouTubers upload a video and get backlash, they seem to brush it off or respond in a "you're overreacting" kind of way, but Jenna saw fans concerns and addressed it in an open and respectful way. I hate that people feel the need to jump on her about how she treats her dogs. I've met bad dog owners, and she sure as hell isn't a bad owner. She does the best she can for them and I think it'd be great if people could step down off their high horse and remember that she's a person, not just an internet thing you can criticize to your hearts content. Jenna, you're doing great. You and Julien are probably the YouTubers I respect the most. You're both amazing people and dog parents and anyone who disagrees needs to reexamine themselves and their own faults.
